  64    #Neural net forward function
  65    def neural_net(self, params, t, x):
  66        t = t / self.t_star[-1]
  67        z = jnp.stack([t, x])
  68        _, outputs = self.state.apply_fn(params, z)
  69        u1 = outputs[0]
  70        u2 = outputs[1]
  71        return u1, u2

  73    #1st coordinate neural net forward function
  74    def u1_net(self, params, t, x):
  75        u1, _ = self.neural_net(params, t, x)
  76        return u1

  83    #Residual operator
  84    def r_net(self, params, t, x):
  85        #Derivatives in x and t
  86        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
  87        u1_t = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
  88        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
  89        u2_t = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
  90
  91        #Two derivatives in x
  92        u1_xx = hessian(self.u1_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
  93        u2_xx = hessian(self.u2_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
  94
  95        #Each coordinate of residual operator
  96        return (u1_t - u1_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2, (u2_t - u2_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2

 108    #Right Dirichlet Condition residual
 109    def res_right_dirichlet(self, params, t, x):
 110        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
 111        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 112        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 113        #Return residual
 114        return (u1 - self.rd[0]) ** 2 + (u2 - self.rd[1]) ** 2
 115
 116    #Right Dirichlet Condition residual non-vectorised
 117    def res_right_dirichlet_nv(self, params, t, x):
 118        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
 119        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
 120        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
 121        #Return residual
 122        return (u1 - self.rd[0]) ** 2 + (u2 - self.rd[1]) ** 2
 123
 124    #Left Dirichlet Condition residual
 125    def res_left_dirichlet(self, params, t, x):
 126        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
 127        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 128        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 129        #Return residual
 130        return (jnp.sqrt(u1  ** 2 + u2 ** 2) - self.radius) ** 2
 131
 132    #Left Dirichlet Condition residual non-vectorised
 133    def res_left_dirichlet_nv(self, params, t, x):
 134        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
 135        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
 136        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
 137        #Return residual
 138        return (jnp.sqrt(u1  ** 2 + u2 ** 2) - self.radius) ** 2
 139
 140    #Neumman condition residual non-vectorised
 141    def res_neumann_nv(self, params, t, x):
 142        #Apply neural net
 143        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
 144        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
 145
 146        #Derivatives in x
 147        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
 148        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
 149
 150        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
 151        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2) ** 2)) + 1e-5)
 152
 153        #Normal at u(x,y)
 154        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
 155
 156        #Return inner product
 157        return jnp.sum(nS * nu) ** 2
 158
 159    #Neumman condition residual
 160    def res_neumann(self, params, t, x):
 161        #Apply neural net to points in the boundary
 162        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 163        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 164
 165        #Derivatives in x
 166        u1_x = self.u1_bound_x(params, t, x)
 167        u2_x = self.u2_bound_x(params, t, x)
 168
 169        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
 170        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2,1)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2,1) ** 2,1)).reshape(u1.shape[0],1) + 1e-5)
 171
 172        #Normal at u(x,y)
 173        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x,1)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
 174
 175        #Return inner product
 176        return jnp.sum(nS * nu,1).reshape(u1.shape[0],1) ** 2

 178    #Compute residuals with causal weights
 179    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
 180    def res_causal(self, params, batch):
 181        # Sort temporal coordinates
 182        t_sorted = batch[:, 0].sort()
 183
 184        #Compute residuals
 185        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(params, t_sorted, batch[:, 1])
 186
 187        #Reshape
 188        res_pred1 = res_pred1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 189        res_pred2 = res_pred2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 190
 191        #Compute mean residuals
 192        res_l1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2, axis=1)
 193        res_l2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2, axis=1)
 194
 195        #Compute weights
 196        res_gamma1 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l1)))
 197        res_gamma2 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l2)))
 198
 199        # Take minimum of the causal weights
 200        gamma = jnp.vstack([res_gamma1,res_gamma2])
 201        gamma = gamma.min(0)
 202
 203        return res_l1, res_l2, gamma
 204
 205    #Compute losses
 206    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
 207    def losses(self, params, batch):
 208        # Initial conditions loss
 209        u1_pred = self.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 210        u2_pred = self.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 211        u1_0,u2_0 = self.uinitial(batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 212
 213        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - u1_0) ** 2)
 214        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - u2_0) ** 2)
 215
 216        # Residual loss
 217        if self.config.weighting.use_causal == True:
 218            res_l1, res_l2, gamma = self.res_causal(params, batch)
 219            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_l1 * gamma)
 220            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_l2 * gamma)
 221        else:
 222            res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(
 223                params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 224            )
 225            # Compute loss
 226            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
 227            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
 228
 229        loss_dict = {
 230            "ic": u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss,
 231            "res1": res_loss1,
 232            "res2": res_loss2,
 233            'rd': jnp.mean(self.res_right_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)),
 234            'ld': jnp.mean(self.res_left_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)),
 235            'ln': jnp.mean(self.res_neumann(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl))
 236        }
 237        return loss_dict
 238
 239    #Compute NTK
 240    @partial(jit, static_argnums = (0,))
 241    def compute_diag_ntk(self, params, batch):
 242        #Initial Condition
 243        u1_ic_ntk = vmap(
 244            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
 245        )(self.u1_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 246
 247        u2_ic_ntk = vmap(
 248            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
 249        )(self.u2_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 250
 251        #Right Dirichlet
 252        rd_ntk = vmap(
 253            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
 254        )(self.res_right_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
 255
 256        #Left Dirichlet
 257        ld_ntk = vmap(
 258            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
 259        )(self.res_left_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)
 260
 261        #Left neumann
 262        ln_ntk = vmap(
 263            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
 264        )(self.res_neumann_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)
 265
 266        # Consider the effect of causal weights
 267        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
 268            batch = jnp.array([batch[:, 0].sort(), batch[:, 1]]).T
 269            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
 270                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 271            )
 272
 273            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
 274                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 275            )
 276
 277            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 278            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 279
 280            res_ntk1 = jnp.mean(res_ntk1, axis=1)
 281            res_ntk2 = jnp.mean(res_ntk2, axis=1)
 282
 283            _,_, casual_weights = self.res_causal(params, batch)
 284            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1 * casual_weights
 285            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2 * casual_weights
 286        else:
 287            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
 288                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 289            )
 290            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
 291                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 292            )
 293
 294        ntk_dict = {
 295            "ic": u1_ic_ntk + u2_ic_ntk,
 296            "res1": res_ntk1,
 297            "res2": res_ntk2,
 298            'rd': rd_ntk,
 299            'ld': ld_ntk,
 300            'ln': ln_ntk
 301        }
 302        return ntk_dict

 304class DN_csf_Evaluator(BaseEvaluator):
 305    def __init__(self, config, model, x0_test, tb_test, xc_test, tc_test, u1_0_test, u2_0_test):
 306        super().__init__(config, model)
 307
 308        self.x0_test = x0_test
 309        self.tb_test = tb_test
 310        self.xc_test = xc_test
 311        self.tc_test = tc_test
 312        self.u2_0_test = u2_0_test
 313        self.u1_0_test = u1_0_test
 314
 315    def log_errors(self, params):
 316        u1_pred = self.model.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, self.x0_test)
 317        u2_pred = self.model.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, self.x0_test)
 318
 319        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - self.u1_0_test) ** 2)
 320        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - self.u2_0_test) ** 2)
 321
 322        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.model.r_pred_fn(
 323            params, self.tc_test[:,0], self.xc_test[:,0]
 324        )
 325        res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
 326        res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
 327
 328        self.log_dict["ic_rel_test"] = jnp.sqrt((u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss)/(jnp.mean(self.u1_0_test ** 2) + jnp.mean(self.u2_0_test ** 2)))
 329        self.log_dict["res1_test"] = res_loss1
 330        self.log_dict["res2_test"] = res_loss2
 331        self.log_dict["rd_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_right_dirichlet(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xu))
 332        self.log_dict["ld_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_left_dirichlet(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xl))
 333        self.log_dict["ln_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_neumann(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xl))
 334
 335    def __call__(self, state, batch):
 336        self.log_dict = super().__call__(state, batch)
 337
 338        if self.config.logging.log_errors:
 339            self.log_errors(state.params)
 340
 341        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
 342            _, _, causal_weight = self.model.res_causal(state.params, batch)
 343            self.log_dict["cas_weight"] = causal_weight.min()
 344
 345        return self.log_dict

 423
 424        #Each coordinate of residual operator
 425        return (u1_t - u1_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2, (u2_t - u2_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2
 426
 427    #1st coordinate residual operator
 428    def r_net1(self, params, t, x):
 429        r1,_ = self.r_net(params, t, x)
 430        return r1
 431
 432    #2nd coordinate residual operator
 433    def r_net2(self, params, t, x):
 434        _,r2 = self.r_net(params, t, x)
 435        return r2
 436
 437    #Right Dirichlet Condition residual
 438    def res_dirichlet(self, params, t, x):
 439        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
 440        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 441        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 442        #Return residual
 443        return (jnp.sqrt(u1  ** 2 + u2 ** 2) - self.radius) ** 2
 444
 445    #Right Dirichlet Condition residual non-vectorised
 446    def res_dirichlet_nv(self, params, t, x):
 447        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
 448        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
 449        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
 450        #Return residual
 451        return (jnp.sqrt(u1  ** 2 + u2 ** 2) - self.radius) ** 2
 452
 453    #Neumman condition residual non-vectorised
 454    def res_neumann_nv(self, params, t, x):
 455        #Apply neural net
 456        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
 457        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
 458
 459        #Derivatives in x
 460        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
 461        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
 462
 463        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
 464        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2) ** 2)) + 1e-5)
 465
 466        #Normal at u(x,y)
 467        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
 468
 469        #Return inner product
 470        return jnp.sum(nS * nu) ** 2
 471
 472    #Neumman condition residual
 473    def res_neumann(self, params, t, x):
 474        #Apply neural net to points in the boundary
 475        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 476        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 477
 478        #Derivatives in x
 479        u1_x = self.u1_bound_x(params, t, x)
 480        u2_x = self.u2_bound_x(params, t, x)
 481
 482        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
 483        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2,1)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2,1) ** 2,1)).reshape(u1.shape[0],1) + 1e-5)
 484
 485        #Normal at u(x,y)
 486        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x,1)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
 487
 488        #Return inner product
 489        return jnp.sum(nS * nu,1).reshape(u1.shape[0],1) ** 2
 490
 491    #Compute residuals with causal weights
 492    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
 493    def res_causal(self, params, batch):
 494        # Sort temporal coordinates
 495        t_sorted = batch[:, 0].sort()
 496
 497        #Compute residuals
 498        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(params, t_sorted, batch[:, 1])
 499
 500        #Reshape
 501        res_pred1 = res_pred1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 502        res_pred2 = res_pred2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 503
 504        #Compute mean residuals
 505        res_l1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2, axis=1)
 506        res_l2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2, axis=1)
 507
 508        #Compute weights
 509        res_gamma1 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l1)))
 510        res_gamma2 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l2)))
 511
 512        # Take minimum of the causal weights
 513        gamma = jnp.vstack([res_gamma1,res_gamma2])
 514        gamma = gamma.min(0)
 515
 516        return res_l1, res_l2, gamma
 517
 518    #Compute losses
 519    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
 520    def losses(self, params, batch):
 521        # Initial conditions loss
 522        u1_pred = self.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 523        u2_pred = self.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 524        u1_0,u2_0 = self.uinitial(batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 525
 526        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - u1_0) ** 2)
 527        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - u2_0) ** 2)
 528
 529        # Residual loss
 530        if self.config.weighting.use_causal == True:
 531            res_l1, res_l2, gamma = self.res_causal(params, batch)
 532            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_l1 * gamma)
 533            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_l2 * gamma)
 534        else:
 535            res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(
 536                params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 537            )
 538            # Compute loss
 539            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
 540            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
 541
 542        loss_dict = {
 543            "ic": u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss,
 544            "res1": res_loss1,
 545            "res2": res_loss2,
 546            'rd': jnp.mean(self.res_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)),
 547            'ld': jnp.mean(self.res_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)),
 548            'ln': jnp.mean(self.res_neumann(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)),
 549            'rn': jnp.mean(self.res_neumann(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu))
 550        }
 551        return loss_dict
 552
 553    #Compute NTK
 554    @partial(jit, static_argnums = (0,))
 555    def compute_diag_ntk(self, params, batch):
 556        #Initial Condition
 557        u1_ic_ntk = vmap(
 558            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
 559        )(self.u1_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 560
 561        u2_ic_ntk = vmap(
 562            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
 563        )(self.u2_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
 564
 565        #Right Dirichlet
 566        rd_ntk = vmap(
 567            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
 568        )(self.res_right_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
 569
 570        #Dirichlet
 571        ld_ntk = vmap(
 572            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
 573        )(self.res_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)
 574        rd_ntk = vmap(
 575            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
 576        )(self.res_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
 577
 578        #Left neumann
 579        ln_ntk = vmap(
 580            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
 581        )(self.res_neumann_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)
 582        rn_ntk = vmap(
 583            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
 584        )(self.res_neumann_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
 585
 586        # Consider the effect of causal weights
 587        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
 588            batch = jnp.array([batch[:, 0].sort(), batch[:, 1]]).T
 589            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
 590                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 591            )
 592
 593            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
 594                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 595            )
 596
 597            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 598            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 599
 600            res_ntk1 = jnp.mean(res_ntk1, axis=1)
 601            res_ntk2 = jnp.mean(res_ntk2, axis=1)
 602
 603            _,_, casual_weights = self.res_causal(params, batch)
 604            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1 * casual_weights
 605            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2 * casual_weights
 606        else:
 607            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
 608                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 609            )
 610            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
 611                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 612            )
 613
 614        ntk_dict = {
 615            "ic": u1_ic_ntk + u2_ic_ntk,
 616            "res1": res_ntk1,
 617            "res2": res_ntk2,
 618            'rd': rd_ntk,
 619            'ld': ld_ntk,
 620            'ln': ln_ntk,
 621            'rn': rn_ntk
 622        }
 623        return ntk_dict
 624
 625class NN_csf_Evaluator(BaseEvaluator):
 626    def __init__(self, config, model, x0_test, tb_test, xc_test, tc_test, u1_0_test, u2_0_test):
 627        super().__init__(config, model)
 628
 629        self.x0_test = x0_test
 630        self.tb_test = tb_test
 631        self.xc_test = xc_test
 632        self.tc_test = tc_test
 633        self.u2_0_test = u2_0_test
 634        self.u1_0_test = u1_0_test
 635
 636    def log_errors(self, params):
 637        u1_pred = self.model.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, self.x0_test)
 638        u2_pred = self.model.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, self.x0_test)
 639
 640        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - self.u1_0_test) ** 2)
 641        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - self.u2_0_test) ** 2)
 642
 643        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.model.r_pred_fn(
 644            params, self.tc_test[:,0], self.xc_test[:,0]
 645        )
 646        res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
 647        res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
 648
 649        self.log_dict["ic_rel_test"] = jnp.sqrt((u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss)/(jnp.mean(self.u1_0_test ** 2) + jnp.mean(self.u2_0_test ** 2)))
 650        self.log_dict["res1_test"] = res_loss1
 651        self.log_dict["res2_test"] = res_loss2
 652        self.log_dict["rd_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_dirichlet(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xu))
 653        self.log_dict["ld_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_dirichlet(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xl))
 654        self.log_dict["ln_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_neumann(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xl))
 655        self.log_dict["rn_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_neumann(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xu))
 656
 657    def __call__(self, state, batch):
 658        self.log_dict = super().__call__(state, batch)
 659
 660        if self.config.logging.log_errors:
 661            self.log_errors(state.params)
 662
 663        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
 664            _, _, causal_weight = self.model.res_causal(state.params, batch)
 665            self.log_dict["cas_weight"] = causal_weight.min()
 666
 667        return self.log_dict

 669class DD_csf(ForwardIVP):
 670    def __init__(self, config, uinitial, t_star):
 671        super().__init__(config)
 672
 673        #Grid of time
 674        self.t_star = t_star
 675
 676        #Initial condition function
 677        self.uinitial = uinitial
 678
 679        #Boundary points
 680        self.xl = config.xl
 681        self.xu = config.xu
 682
 683        #Right dirichlet point
 684        self.ld = config.ld
 685        self.rd = config.rd
 686
 687        # Predictions over array of x fot t fixed
 688        self.u1_0_pred_fn = vmap(
 689            vmap(self.u1_net, (None, None, 0)), (None, None, 0)
 690        )
 691        self.u2_0_pred_fn = vmap(
 692            vmap(self.u2_net, (None, None, 0)), (None, None, 0)
 693        )
 694
 695        #Prediction over array of t for x fixed
 696        self.u2_bound_pred_fn = vmap(
 697            vmap(self.u2_net, (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None)
 698        )
 699
 700        self.u1_bound_pred_fn = vmap(
 701            vmap(self.u1_net, (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None)
 702        )
 703
 704        #Vmap neural net
 705        self.u1_pred_fn = vmap(self.u1_net, (None, 0, 0))
 706
 707        self.u2_pred_fn = vmap(self.u2_net, (None, 0, 0))
 708
 709        #Vmap residual operator
 710        self.r_pred_fn = vmap(self.r_net, (None, 0, 0))
 711
 712        #Derivatives on x for x fixed and t in a array
 713        self.u1_bound_x = vmap(vmap(grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2), (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None))
 714        self.u2_bound_x = vmap(vmap(grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2), (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None))
 715
 716    #Neural net forward function
 717    def neural_net(self, params, t, x):
 718        t = t / self.t_star[-1]
 719        z = jnp.stack([t, x])
 720        _, outputs = self.state.apply_fn(params, z)
 721        u1 = outputs[0]
 722        u2 = outputs[1]
 723        return u1, u2
 724
 725    #1st coordinate neural net forward function
 726    def u1_net(self, params, t, x):
 727        u1, _ = self.neural_net(params, t, x)
 728        return u1
 729
 730    #2st coordinate neural net forward function
 731    def u2_net(self, params, t, x):
 732        _, u2 = self.neural_net(params, t, x)
 733        return u2
 734
 735    #Residual operator
 736    def r_net(self, params, t, x):
 737        #Derivatives in x and t
 738        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
 739        u1_t = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
 740        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
 741        u2_t = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
 742
 743        #Two derivatives in x
 744        u1_xx = hessian(self.u1_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
 745        u2_xx = hessian(self.u2_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
 746
 747        #Each coordinate of residual operator
 748        return (u1_t - u1_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2, (u2_t - u2_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2
 749
 750    #1st coordinate residual operator
 751    def r_net1(self, params, t, x):
 752        r1,_ = self.r_net(params, t, x)
 753        return r1
 754
 755    #2nd coordinate residual operator
 756    def r_net2(self, params, t, x):
 757        _,r2 = self.r_net(params, t, x)
 758        return r2

 764        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
 765        #Return residual
 766        return (u1 - self.rd[0]) ** 2 + (u2 - self.rd[1]) ** 2

 792    #Compute residuals with causal weights
 793    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
 794    def res_causal(self, params, batch):
 795        # Sort temporal coordinates
 796        t_sorted = batch[:, 0].sort()
 797
 798        #Compute residuals
 799        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(params, t_sorted, batch[:, 1])
 800
 801        #Reshape
 802        res_pred1 = res_pred1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 803        res_pred2 = res_pred2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
 804
 805        #Compute mean residuals
 806        res_l1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2, axis=1)
 807        res_l2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2, axis=1)
 808
 809        #Compute weights
 810        res_gamma1 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l1)))
 811        res_gamma2 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l2)))
 812
 813        # Take minimum of the causal weights

 819    #Compute losses

 824        u2_pred = self.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))

 834            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_l2 * gamma)

 837                params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
 838            )
 839            # Compute loss
 840            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
 841            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)

 844            "ic": u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss,

 848            'ld': jnp.mean(self.res_left_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl))

 869        #Left Dirichlet

 953class closed_csf(ForwardIVP):
 954    def __init__(self, config, uinitial, t_star):
 955        super().__init__(config)
 956
 957        #Grid of time
 958        self.t_star = t_star
 959
 960        #Initial condition function
 961        self.uinitial = uinitial
 962
 963        #Boundary points
 964        self.xl = config.xl
 965        self.xu = config.xu
 966
 967        # Predictions over array of x fot t fixed
 968        self.u1_0_pred_fn = vmap(
 969            vmap(self.u1_net, (None, None, 0)), (None, None, 0)
 970        )
 971        self.u2_0_pred_fn = vmap(
 972            vmap(self.u2_net, (None, None, 0)), (None, None, 0)
 973        )
 974
 975        #Prediction over array of t for x fixed
 976        self.u2_bound_pred_fn = vmap(
 977            vmap(self.u2_net, (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None)

 988

 990        self.r_pred_fn = vmap(self.r_net, (None, 0, 0))
 991
 992        #Derivatives on x for x fixed and t in a array
 993        self.u1_bound_x = vmap(vmap(grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2), (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None))
 994        self.u2_bound_x = vmap(vmap(grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2), (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None))

 996    #Neural net forward function
 997    def neural_net(self, params, t, x):
 998        t = t / self.t_star[-1]
 999        z = jnp.stack([t, x])
1000        _, outputs = self.state.apply_fn(params, z)
1001        u1 = outputs[0]
1002        u2 = outputs[1]
1003        return u1, u2

1005    #1st coordinate neural net forward function
1006    def u1_net(self, params, t, x):
1007        u1, _ = self.neural_net(params, t, x)
1008        return u1
1009
1010    #2st coordinate neural net forward function
1011    def u2_net(self, params, t, x):
1012        _, u2 = self.neural_net(params, t, x)
1013        return u2

1015    #Residual operator
1016    def r_net(self, params, t, x):
1017        #Derivatives in x and t
1018        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
1019        u1_t = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
1020        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
1021        u2_t = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
1022
1023        #Two derivatives in x
1024        u1_xx = hessian(self.u1_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
1025        u2_xx = hessian(self.u2_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
1026
1027        #Each coordinate of residual operator
1028        return (u1_t - u1_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2, (u2_t - u2_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2
1029
1030    #1st coordinate residual operator
1031    def r_net1(self, params, t, x):
1032        r1,_ = self.r_net(params, t, x)
1033        return r1
1034
1035    #2nd coordinate residual operator
1036    def r_net2(self, params, t, x):
1037        _,r2 = self.r_net(params, t, x)
1038        return r2

1040    #Compute residuals with causal weights
1041    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
1042    def res_causal(self, params, batch):
1043        # Sort temporal coordinates
1044        t_sorted = batch[:, 0].sort()
1045
1046        #Compute residuals
1047        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(params, t_sorted, batch[:, 1])
1048
1049        #Reshape
1050        res_pred1 = res_pred1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
1051        res_pred2 = res_pred2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
1052
1053        #Compute mean residuals
1054        res_l1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2, axis=1)
1055        res_l2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2, axis=1)
1056
1057        #Compute weights
1058        res_gamma1 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l1)))
1059        res_gamma2 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l2)))
1060
1061        # Take minimum of the causal weights
1062        gamma = jnp.vstack([res_gamma1,res_gamma2])
1063        gamma = gamma.min(0)
1064
1065        return res_l1, res_l2, gamma
1066
1067    #Compute losses
1068    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
1069    def losses(self, params, batch):
1070        # Initial conditions loss
1071        u1_pred = self.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
1072        u2_pred = self.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
1073        u1_0,u2_0 = self.uinitial(batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
1074
1075        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - u1_0) ** 2)
1076        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - u2_0) ** 2)
1077
1078        # Residual loss
1079        if self.config.weighting.use_causal == True:
1080            res_l1, res_l2, gamma = self.res_causal(params, batch)
1081            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_l1 * gamma)
1082            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_l2 * gamma)
1083        else:
1084            res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(
1085                params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
1086            )
1087            # Compute loss
1088            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
1089            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
1090
1091        loss_dict = {
1092            "ic": u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss,
1093            "res1": res_loss1,
1094            "res2": res_loss2
1095        }
1096        return loss_dict
1097
1098    #Compute NTK
1099    @partial(jit, static_argnums = (0,))
1100    def compute_diag_ntk(self, params, batch):
1101        #Initial Condition
1102        u1_ic_ntk = vmap(
1103            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
1104        )(self.u1_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
1105
1106        u2_ic_ntk = vmap(
1107            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
1108        )(self.u2_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
1109
1110        # Consider the effect of causal weights
1111        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
1112            batch = jnp.array([batch[:, 0].sort(), batch[:, 1]]).T
1113            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
1114                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
1115            )
1116
1117            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
1118                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
1119            )
1120
1121            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
1122            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
1123
1124            res_ntk1 = jnp.mean(res_ntk1, axis=1)
1125            res_ntk2 = jnp.mean(res_ntk2, axis=1)
1126
1127            _,_, casual_weights = self.res_causal(params, batch)
1128            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1 * casual_weights
1129            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2 * casual_weights
1130        else:
1131            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
1132                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
1133            )
1134            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
1135                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
1136            )
1137
1138        ntk_dict = {
1139            "ic": u1_ic_ntk + u2_ic_ntk,
1140            "res1": res_ntk1,
1141            "res2": res_ntk2
1142        }
1143        return ntk_dict

141    #Neumman condition residual non-vectorised
142    def res_neumann_nv(self, params, t, x):
143        #Apply neural net
144        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
145        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
146
147        #Derivatives in x
148        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
149        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
150
151        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
152        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2) ** 2)) + 1e-5)
153
154        #Normal at u(x,y)
155        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
156
157        #Return inner product
158        return jnp.sum(nS * nu) ** 2

163        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)

165

168        u2_x = self.u2_bound_x(params, t, x)
169
170        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
171        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2,1)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2,1) ** 2,1)).reshape(u1.shape[0],1) + 1e-5)
172
173        #Normal at u(x,y)
174        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x,1)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
175
176        #Return inner product

208    def losses(self, params, batch):
209        # Initial conditions loss

211        u2_pred = self.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))

216

218        if self.config.weighting.use_causal == True:
219            res_l1, res_l2, gamma = self.res_causal(params, batch)
220            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_l1 * gamma)
221            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_l2 * gamma)
222        else:
223            res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(
224                params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]

227            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
228            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
229
230        loss_dict = {
231            "ic": u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss,
232            "res1": res_loss1,
233            "res2": res_loss2,
234            'rd': jnp.mean(self.res_right_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)),
235            'ld': jnp.mean(self.res_left_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)),
236            'ln': jnp.mean(self.res_neumann(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl))
237        }
238        return loss_dict

85    def r_net(self, params, t, x):
86        #Derivatives in x and t
87        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
88        u1_t = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
89        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
90        u2_t = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
91
92        #Two derivatives in x
93        u1_xx = hessian(self.u1_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
94        u2_xx = hessian(self.u2_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
95
96        #Each coordinate of residual operator
97        return (u1_t - u1_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2, (u2_t - u2_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2

def res_neumann_nv(self, params, t, x): 
142    def res_neumann_nv(self, params, t, x):
143        #Apply neural net
144        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
145        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
146
147        #Derivatives in x
148        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
149        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
150
151        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
152        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2) ** 2)) + 1e-5)
153
154        #Normal at u(x,y)
155        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
156
157        #Return inner product
158        return jnp.sum(nS * nu) ** 2
def res_neumann(self, params, t, x): 
161    def res_neumann(self, params, t, x):
162        #Apply neural net to points in the boundary
163        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
164        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
165
166        #Derivatives in x
167        u1_x = self.u1_bound_x(params, t, x)
168        u2_x = self.u2_bound_x(params, t, x)
169
170        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
171        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2,1)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2,1) ** 2,1)).reshape(u1.shape[0],1) + 1e-5)
172
173        #Normal at u(x,y)
174        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x,1)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
175
176        #Return inner product
177        return jnp.sum(nS * nu,1).reshape(u1.shape[0],1) ** 2
@partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
def res_causal(self, params, batch): 
180    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
181    def res_causal(self, params, batch):
182        # Sort temporal coordinates
183        t_sorted = batch[:, 0].sort()
184
185        #Compute residuals
186        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(params, t_sorted, batch[:, 1])
187
188        #Reshape
189        res_pred1 = res_pred1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
190        res_pred2 = res_pred2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
191
192        #Compute mean residuals
193        res_l1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2, axis=1)
194        res_l2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2, axis=1)
195
196        #Compute weights
197        res_gamma1 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l1)))
198        res_gamma2 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l2)))
199
200        # Take minimum of the causal weights
201        gamma = jnp.vstack([res_gamma1,res_gamma2])
202        gamma = gamma.min(0)
203
204        return res_l1, res_l2, gamma

225            )

228            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
229

232            "res1": res_loss1,
233            "res2": res_loss2,

375            vmap(self.u2_net, (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None)
376        )
377
378        self.u1_bound_pred_fn = vmap(
379            vmap(self.u1_net, (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None)
380        )
381
382        #Vmap neural net
383        self.u1_pred_fn = vmap(self.u1_net, (None, 0, 0))
384
385        self.u2_pred_fn = vmap(self.u2_net, (None, 0, 0))
386
387        #Vmap residual operator
388        self.r_pred_fn = vmap(self.r_net, (None, 0, 0))
389
390        #Derivatives on x for x fixed and t in a array
391        self.u1_bound_x = vmap(vmap(grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2), (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None))
392        self.u2_bound_x = vmap(vmap(grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2), (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None))
393
394    #Neural net forward function
395    def neural_net(self, params, t, x):
396        t = t / self.t_star[-1]
397        z = jnp.stack([t, x])
398        _, outputs = self.state.apply_fn(params, z)
399        u1 = outputs[0]
400        u2 = outputs[1]
401        return u1, u2
402
403    #1st coordinate neural net forward function
404    def u1_net(self, params, t, x):
405        u1, _ = self.neural_net(params, t, x)
406        return u1
407
408    #2st coordinate neural net forward function
409    def u2_net(self, params, t, x):
410        _, u2 = self.neural_net(params, t, x)
411        return u2
412
413    #Residual operator
414    def r_net(self, params, t, x):
415        #Derivatives in x and t
416        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
417        u1_t = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
418        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
419        u2_t = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
420
421        #Two derivatives in x
422        u1_xx = hessian(self.u1_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
423        u2_xx = hessian(self.u2_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
424
425        #Each coordinate of residual operator
426        return (u1_t - u1_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2, (u2_t - u2_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2
427
428    #1st coordinate residual operator
429    def r_net1(self, params, t, x):
430        r1,_ = self.r_net(params, t, x)
431        return r1
432
433    #2nd coordinate residual operator
434    def r_net2(self, params, t, x):
435        _,r2 = self.r_net(params, t, x)
436        return r2
437
438    #Right Dirichlet Condition residual
439    def res_dirichlet(self, params, t, x):
440        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
441        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
442        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
443        #Return residual
444        return (jnp.sqrt(u1  ** 2 + u2 ** 2) - self.radius) ** 2
445
446    #Right Dirichlet Condition residual non-vectorised
447    def res_dirichlet_nv(self, params, t, x):
448        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
449        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
450        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
451        #Return residual
452        return (jnp.sqrt(u1  ** 2 + u2 ** 2) - self.radius) ** 2
453
454    #Neumman condition residual non-vectorised
455    def res_neumann_nv(self, params, t, x):
456        #Apply neural net
457        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
458        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
459
460        #Derivatives in x
461        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
462        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
463
464        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
465        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2) ** 2)) + 1e-5)
466
467        #Normal at u(x,y)
468        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
469
470        #Return inner product
471        return jnp.sum(nS * nu) ** 2
472
473    #Neumman condition residual
474    def res_neumann(self, params, t, x):
475        #Apply neural net to points in the boundary
476        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
477        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
478
479        #Derivatives in x
480        u1_x = self.u1_bound_x(params, t, x)
481        u2_x = self.u2_bound_x(params, t, x)
482
483        #Assuming that u(x,t) \in S, compute the vector normal to S at u(x,t)
484        nS = jnp.append(u1,u2,1)/(jnp.sqrt(jnp.sum(jnp.append(u1,u2,1) ** 2,1)).reshape(u1.shape[0],1) + 1e-5)
485
486        #Normal at u(x,y)
487        nu = jnp.append(u2_x,(-1)*u1_x,1)/(jnp.sqrt(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2) + 1e-5)
488
489        #Return inner product
490        return jnp.sum(nS * nu,1).reshape(u1.shape[0],1) ** 2
491
492    #Compute residuals with causal weights
493    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
494    def res_causal(self, params, batch):
495        # Sort temporal coordinates
496        t_sorted = batch[:, 0].sort()
497
498        #Compute residuals
499        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(params, t_sorted, batch[:, 1])
500
501        #Reshape
502        res_pred1 = res_pred1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
503        res_pred2 = res_pred2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
504
505        #Compute mean residuals
506        res_l1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2, axis=1)
507        res_l2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2, axis=1)
508
509        #Compute weights
510        res_gamma1 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l1)))
511        res_gamma2 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l2)))
512
513        # Take minimum of the causal weights
514        gamma = jnp.vstack([res_gamma1,res_gamma2])
515        gamma = gamma.min(0)
516
517        return res_l1, res_l2, gamma
518
519    #Compute losses
520    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
521    def losses(self, params, batch):
522        # Initial conditions loss
523        u1_pred = self.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
524        u2_pred = self.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
525        u1_0,u2_0 = self.uinitial(batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
526
527        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - u1_0) ** 2)
528        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - u2_0) ** 2)
529
530        # Residual loss
531        if self.config.weighting.use_causal == True:
532            res_l1, res_l2, gamma = self.res_causal(params, batch)
533            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_l1 * gamma)
534            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_l2 * gamma)
535        else:
536            res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(
537                params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
538            )
539            # Compute loss
540            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
541            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
542
543        loss_dict = {
544            "ic": u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss,
545            "res1": res_loss1,
546            "res2": res_loss2,
547            'rd': jnp.mean(self.res_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)),
548            'ld': jnp.mean(self.res_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)),
549            'ln': jnp.mean(self.res_neumann(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)),
550            'rn': jnp.mean(self.res_neumann(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu))
551        }
552        return loss_dict
553
554    #Compute NTK
555    @partial(jit, static_argnums = (0,))
556    def compute_diag_ntk(self, params, batch):
557        #Initial Condition
558        u1_ic_ntk = vmap(
559            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
560        )(self.u1_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
561
562        u2_ic_ntk = vmap(
563            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
564        )(self.u2_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
565
566        #Right Dirichlet
567        rd_ntk = vmap(
568            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
569        )(self.res_right_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
570
571        #Dirichlet
572        ld_ntk = vmap(
573            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
574        )(self.res_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)
575        rd_ntk = vmap(
576            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
577        )(self.res_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
578
579        #Left neumann
580        ln_ntk = vmap(
581            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
582        )(self.res_neumann_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)
583        rn_ntk = vmap(
584            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
585        )(self.res_neumann_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
586
587        # Consider the effect of causal weights
588        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
589            batch = jnp.array([batch[:, 0].sort(), batch[:, 1]]).T
590            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
591                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
592            )
593
594            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
595                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
596            )
597
598            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
599            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
600
601            res_ntk1 = jnp.mean(res_ntk1, axis=1)
602            res_ntk2 = jnp.mean(res_ntk2, axis=1)
603
604            _,_, casual_weights = self.res_causal(params, batch)
605            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1 * casual_weights
606            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2 * casual_weights
607        else:
608            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
609                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
610            )
611            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
612                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
613            )
614
615        ntk_dict = {
616            "ic": u1_ic_ntk + u2_ic_ntk,
617            "res1": res_ntk1,
618            "res2": res_ntk2,
619            'rd': rd_ntk,
620            'ld': ld_ntk,
621            'ln': ln_ntk,
622            'rn': rn_ntk
623        }
624        return ntk_dict

577        )(self.res_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
578
579        #Left neumann
580        ln_ntk = vmap(
581            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
582        )(self.res_neumann_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)
583        rn_ntk = vmap(
584            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
585        )(self.res_neumann_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
586
587        # Consider the effect of causal weights
588        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
589            batch = jnp.array([batch[:, 0].sort(), batch[:, 1]]).T
590            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
591                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
592            )
593
594            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
595                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
596            )
597
598            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
599            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
600
601            res_ntk1 = jnp.mean(res_ntk1, axis=1)
602            res_ntk2 = jnp.mean(res_ntk2, axis=1)
603
604            _,_, casual_weights = self.res_causal(params, batch)
605            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1 * casual_weights
606            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2 * casual_weights
607        else:
608            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
609                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
610            )
611            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
612                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
613            )
614
615        ntk_dict = {
616            "ic": u1_ic_ntk + u2_ic_ntk,
617            "res1": res_ntk1,
618            "res2": res_ntk2,
619            'rd': rd_ntk,
620            'ld': ld_ntk,
621            'ln': ln_ntk,
622            'rn': rn_ntk
623        }
624        return ntk_dict
class NN_csf_Evaluator(jaxpi.evaluator.BaseEvaluator): 
626class NN_csf_Evaluator(BaseEvaluator):
627    def __init__(self, config, model, x0_test, tb_test, xc_test, tc_test, u1_0_test, u2_0_test):
628        super().__init__(config, model)
629
630        self.x0_test = x0_test
631        self.tb_test = tb_test
632        self.xc_test = xc_test
633        self.tc_test = tc_test
634        self.u2_0_test = u2_0_test
635        self.u1_0_test = u1_0_test
636
637    def log_errors(self, params):
638        u1_pred = self.model.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, self.x0_test)
639        u2_pred = self.model.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, self.x0_test)
640
641        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - self.u1_0_test) ** 2)
642        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - self.u2_0_test) ** 2)
643
644        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.model.r_pred_fn(
645            params, self.tc_test[:,0], self.xc_test[:,0]
646        )
647        res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
648        res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
649
650        self.log_dict["ic_rel_test"] = jnp.sqrt((u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss)/(jnp.mean(self.u1_0_test ** 2) + jnp.mean(self.u2_0_test ** 2)))
651        self.log_dict["res1_test"] = res_loss1
652        self.log_dict["res2_test"] = res_loss2
653        self.log_dict["rd_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_dirichlet(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xu))
654        self.log_dict["ld_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_dirichlet(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xl))
655        self.log_dict["ln_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_neumann(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xl))
656        self.log_dict["rn_test"] = jnp.mean(self.model.res_neumann(params, self.tb_test, self.model.xu))
657
658    def __call__(self, state, batch):
659        self.log_dict = super().__call__(state, batch)
660
661        if self.config.logging.log_errors:
662            self.log_errors(state.params)
663
664        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
665            _, _, causal_weight = self.model.res_causal(state.params, batch)
666            self.log_dict["cas_weight"] = causal_weight.min()
667
668        return self.log_dict

class DD_csf(jaxpi.models.ForwardIVP): 
670class DD_csf(ForwardIVP):
671    def __init__(self, config, uinitial, t_star):
672        super().__init__(config)
673
674        #Grid of time
675        self.t_star = t_star
676
677        #Initial condition function
678        self.uinitial = uinitial
679
680        #Boundary points
681        self.xl = config.xl
682        self.xu = config.xu
683
684        #Right dirichlet point
685        self.ld = config.ld
686        self.rd = config.rd
687
688        # Predictions over array of x fot t fixed
689        self.u1_0_pred_fn = vmap(
690            vmap(self.u1_net, (None, None, 0)), (None, None, 0)
691        )
692        self.u2_0_pred_fn = vmap(
693            vmap(self.u2_net, (None, None, 0)), (None, None, 0)
694        )
695
696        #Prediction over array of t for x fixed
697        self.u2_bound_pred_fn = vmap(
698            vmap(self.u2_net, (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None)
699        )
700
701        self.u1_bound_pred_fn = vmap(
702            vmap(self.u1_net, (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None)
703        )
704
705        #Vmap neural net
706        self.u1_pred_fn = vmap(self.u1_net, (None, 0, 0))
707
708        self.u2_pred_fn = vmap(self.u2_net, (None, 0, 0))
709
710        #Vmap residual operator
711        self.r_pred_fn = vmap(self.r_net, (None, 0, 0))
712
713        #Derivatives on x for x fixed and t in a array
714        self.u1_bound_x = vmap(vmap(grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2), (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None))
715        self.u2_bound_x = vmap(vmap(grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2), (None, 0, None)), (None, 0, None))
716
717    #Neural net forward function
718    def neural_net(self, params, t, x):
719        t = t / self.t_star[-1]
720        z = jnp.stack([t, x])
721        _, outputs = self.state.apply_fn(params, z)
722        u1 = outputs[0]
723        u2 = outputs[1]
724        return u1, u2
725
726    #1st coordinate neural net forward function
727    def u1_net(self, params, t, x):
728        u1, _ = self.neural_net(params, t, x)
729        return u1
730
731    #2st coordinate neural net forward function
732    def u2_net(self, params, t, x):
733        _, u2 = self.neural_net(params, t, x)
734        return u2
735
736    #Residual operator
737    def r_net(self, params, t, x):
738        #Derivatives in x and t
739        u1_x = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
740        u1_t = grad(self.u1_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
741        u2_x = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 2)(params, t, x)
742        u2_t = grad(self.u2_net, argnums = 1)(params, t, x)
743
744        #Two derivatives in x
745        u1_xx = hessian(self.u1_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
746        u2_xx = hessian(self.u2_net, argnums = (2))(params, t, x)
747
748        #Each coordinate of residual operator
749        return (u1_t - u1_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2, (u2_t - u2_xx/(u1_x ** 2 + u2_x ** 2 + 1e-5)) ** 2
750
751    #1st coordinate residual operator
752    def r_net1(self, params, t, x):
753        r1,_ = self.r_net(params, t, x)
754        return r1
755
756    #2nd coordinate residual operator
757    def r_net2(self, params, t, x):
758        _,r2 = self.r_net(params, t, x)
759        return r2
760
761    #Right Dirichlet Condition residual
762    def res_right_dirichlet(self, params, t, x):
763        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
764        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
765        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
766        #Return residual
767        return (u1 - self.rd[0]) ** 2 + (u2 - self.rd[1]) ** 2
768
769    #Right Dirichlet Condition residual non-vectorised
770    def res_right_dirichlet_nv(self, params, t, x):
771        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
772        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
773        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
774        #Return residual
775        return (u1 - self.rd[0]) ** 2 + (u2 - self.rd[1]) ** 2
776
777    #Left Dirichlet Condition residual
778    def res_left_dirichlet(self, params, t, x):
779        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
780        u1 = self.u1_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
781        u2 = self.u2_bound_pred_fn(params, t, x)
782        #Return residual
783        return (u1 - self.ld[0]) ** 2 + (u2 - self.ld[1]) ** 2
784
785    #Left Dirichlet Condition residual non-vectorised
786    def res_left_dirichlet_nv(self, params, t, x):
787        #Apply neural net to point in the boundary
788        u1 = self.u1_net(params, t, x)
789        u2 = self.u2_net(params, t, x)
790        #Return residual
791        return (u1 - self.ld[0]) ** 2 + (u2 - self.ld[1]) ** 2
792
793    #Compute residuals with causal weights
794    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
795    def res_causal(self, params, batch):
796        # Sort temporal coordinates
797        t_sorted = batch[:, 0].sort()
798
799        #Compute residuals
800        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(params, t_sorted, batch[:, 1])
801
802        #Reshape
803        res_pred1 = res_pred1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
804        res_pred2 = res_pred2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
805
806        #Compute mean residuals
807        res_l1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2, axis=1)
808        res_l2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2, axis=1)
809
810        #Compute weights
811        res_gamma1 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l1)))
812        res_gamma2 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l2)))
813
814        # Take minimum of the causal weights
815        gamma = jnp.vstack([res_gamma1,res_gamma2])
816        gamma = gamma.min(0)
817
818        return res_l1, res_l2, gamma
819
820    #Compute losses
821    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
822    def losses(self, params, batch):
823        # Initial conditions loss
824        u1_pred = self.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
825        u2_pred = self.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
826        u1_0,u2_0 = self.uinitial(batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
827
828        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - u1_0) ** 2)
829        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - u2_0) ** 2)
830
831        # Residual loss
832        if self.config.weighting.use_causal == True:
833            res_l1, res_l2, gamma = self.res_causal(params, batch)
834            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_l1 * gamma)
835            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_l2 * gamma)
836        else:
837            res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(
838                params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
839            )
840            # Compute loss
841            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
842            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
843
844        loss_dict = {
845            "ic": u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss,
846            "res1": res_loss1,
847            "res2": res_loss2,
848            'rd': jnp.mean(self.res_right_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)),
849            'ld': jnp.mean(self.res_left_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl))
850        }
851        return loss_dict
852
853    #Compute NTK
854    @partial(jit, static_argnums = (0,))
855    def compute_diag_ntk(self, params, batch):
856        #Initial Condition
857        u1_ic_ntk = vmap(
858            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
859        )(self.u1_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
860
861        u2_ic_ntk = vmap(
862            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
863        )(self.u2_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
864
865        #Right Dirichlet
866        rd_ntk = vmap(
867            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
868        )(self.res_right_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
869
870        #Left Dirichlet
871        ld_ntk = vmap(
872            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
873        )(self.res_left_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)
874
875        # Consider the effect of causal weights
876        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
877            batch = jnp.array([batch[:, 0].sort(), batch[:, 1]]).T
878            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
879                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
880            )
881
882            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
883                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
884            )
885
886            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
887            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
888
889            res_ntk1 = jnp.mean(res_ntk1, axis=1)
890            res_ntk2 = jnp.mean(res_ntk2, axis=1)
891
892            _,_, casual_weights = self.res_causal(params, batch)
893            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1 * casual_weights
894            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2 * casual_weights
895        else:
896            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
897                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
898            )
899            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
900                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
901            )
902
903        ntk_dict = {
904            "ic": u1_ic_ntk + u2_ic_ntk,
905            "res1": res_ntk1,
906            "res2": res_ntk2,
907            'rd': rd_ntk,
908            'ld': ld_ntk
909        }
910        return ntk_dict

783        return (u1 - self.ld[0]) ** 2 + (u2 - self.ld[1]) ** 2
def res_left_dirichlet_nv(self, params, t, x):

@partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
def res_causal(self, params, batch): 
794    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
795    def res_causal(self, params, batch):
796        # Sort temporal coordinates
797        t_sorted = batch[:, 0].sort()
798
799        #Compute residuals
800        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(params, t_sorted, batch[:, 1])
801
802        #Reshape
803        res_pred1 = res_pred1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
804        res_pred2 = res_pred2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
805
806        #Compute mean residuals
807        res_l1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2, axis=1)
808        res_l2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2, axis=1)
809
810        #Compute weights
811        res_gamma1 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l1)))
812        res_gamma2 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l2)))
813
814        # Take minimum of the causal weights
815        gamma = jnp.vstack([res_gamma1,res_gamma2])
816        gamma = gamma.min(0)
817
818        return res_l1, res_l2, gamma
@partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
def losses(self, params, batch): 
821    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
822    def losses(self, params, batch):
823        # Initial conditions loss
824        u1_pred = self.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
825        u2_pred = self.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
826        u1_0,u2_0 = self.uinitial(batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
827
828        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - u1_0) ** 2)
829        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - u2_0) ** 2)
830
831        # Residual loss
832        if self.config.weighting.use_causal == True:
833            res_l1, res_l2, gamma = self.res_causal(params, batch)
834            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_l1 * gamma)
835            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_l2 * gamma)
836        else:
837            res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(
838                params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
839            )
840            # Compute loss
841            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
842            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
843
844        loss_dict = {
845            "ic": u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss,
846            "res1": res_loss1,
847            "res2": res_loss2,
848            'rd': jnp.mean(self.res_right_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)),
849            'ld': jnp.mean(self.res_left_dirichlet(params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl))
850        }
851        return loss_dict
@partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
def compute_diag_ntk(self, params, batch): 
854    @partial(jit, static_argnums = (0,))
855    def compute_diag_ntk(self, params, batch):
856        #Initial Condition
857        u1_ic_ntk = vmap(
858            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
859        )(self.u1_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
860
861        u2_ic_ntk = vmap(
862            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, None, 0)), (None, None, None, 0)
863        )(self.u2_net, params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
864
865        #Right Dirichlet
866        rd_ntk = vmap(
867            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
868        )(self.res_right_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xu)
869
870        #Left Dirichlet
871        ld_ntk = vmap(
872            vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, None)), (None, None, 0, None)
873        )(self.res_left_dirichlet_nv, params, batch[:, 0].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)), self.xl)
874
875        # Consider the effect of causal weights
876        if self.config.weighting.use_causal:
877            batch = jnp.array([batch[:, 0].sort(), batch[:, 1]]).T
878            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
879                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
880            )
881
882            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
883                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
884            )
885
886            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
887            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
888
889            res_ntk1 = jnp.mean(res_ntk1, axis=1)
890            res_ntk2 = jnp.mean(res_ntk2, axis=1)
891
892            _,_, casual_weights = self.res_causal(params, batch)
893            res_ntk1 = res_ntk1 * casual_weights
894            res_ntk2 = res_ntk2 * casual_weights
895        else:
896            res_ntk1 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
897                self.r_net1, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
898            )
899            res_ntk2 = vmap(ntk_fn, (None, None, 0, 0))(
900                self.r_net2, params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
901            )
902
903        ntk_dict = {
904            "ic": u1_ic_ntk + u2_ic_ntk,
905            "res1": res_ntk1,
906            "res2": res_ntk2,
907            'rd': rd_ntk,
908            'ld': ld_ntk
909        }
910        return ntk_dict

@partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
def res_causal(self, params, batch): 
1042    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
1043    def res_causal(self, params, batch):
1044        # Sort temporal coordinates
1045        t_sorted = batch[:, 0].sort()
1046
1047        #Compute residuals
1048        res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(params, t_sorted, batch[:, 1])
1049
1050        #Reshape
1051        res_pred1 = res_pred1.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
1052        res_pred2 = res_pred2.reshape(self.num_chunks, -1)
1053
1054        #Compute mean residuals
1055        res_l1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2, axis=1)
1056        res_l2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2, axis=1)
1057
1058        #Compute weights
1059        res_gamma1 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l1)))
1060        res_gamma2 = lax.stop_gradient(jnp.exp(-self.tol * (self.M @ res_l2)))
1061
1062        # Take minimum of the causal weights
1063        gamma = jnp.vstack([res_gamma1,res_gamma2])
1064        gamma = gamma.min(0)
1065
1066        return res_l1, res_l2, gamma
@partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
def losses(self, params, batch): 
1069    @partial(jit, static_argnums=(0,))
1070    def losses(self, params, batch):
1071        # Initial conditions loss
1072        u1_pred = self.u1_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
1073        u2_pred = self.u2_0_pred_fn(params, 0.0, batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
1074        u1_0,u2_0 = self.uinitial(batch[:, 1].reshape((batch.shape[0],1)))
1075
1076        u1_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u1_pred - u1_0) ** 2)
1077        u2_ic_loss = jnp.mean((u2_pred - u2_0) ** 2)
1078
1079        # Residual loss
1080        if self.config.weighting.use_causal == True:
1081            res_l1, res_l2, gamma = self.res_causal(params, batch)
1082            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_l1 * gamma)
1083            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_l2 * gamma)
1084        else:
1085            res_pred1,res_pred2 = self.r_pred_fn(
1086                params, batch[:, 0], batch[:, 1]
1087            )
1088            # Compute loss
1089            res_loss1 = jnp.mean(res_pred1 ** 2)
1090            res_loss2 = jnp.mean(res_pred2 ** 2)
1091
1092        loss_dict = {
1093            "ic": u1_ic_loss + u2_ic_loss,
1094            "res1": res_loss1,
1095            "res2": res_loss2
1096        }
1097        return loss_dict
